ess the public API specifically necessitates it.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Exploring reflection and class loading**\\\\n\\\\nI'm contemplating whether using reflection to set `WrapDynaClass.class$java$util$Map` to null is possible, but it seems like it’s probably not allowed. I’m considering public serialization through a class loader instead. Loading a second copy of `commons-beanutils` with a new class loader and attempting static field null might be a route, but direct reflection with dynamic loading is unsupported. \\\\n\\\\nI wonder if the coverage report misses the test's `forName` due to static fields initializing during the native image build, which could explain report discrepancies.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Analyzing dynamic coverage issues**\\\\n\\\\nI'm pondering whether `newInstance` is covered in the JVM, wondering if the dynamic coverage report might include data from both tests. In a Native Image build, `Class.forName(\\\\\\\"java.util.Map\\\\\\\")` seems constant and optimized, possibly eliminating dynamic access. The coverage tool should ideally capture application class bytecode, but perhaps `class$java$util$Map` is initialized during the image build instead of at runtime.\\\\n\\\\nTo cover calls during runtime, I'd need to reset the static field, but the public API doesn’t support that. Could `--initialize-at-run-time` metadata be an option? I'll need to investigate this further!\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Considering user instructions**\\\\n\\\\nThe user mentioned not to compile or run anything, so I’ll make sure to respect that request. It seems important to avoid any actions that could lead to compiling or executing code. I want to be cautious and ensure I'm following their instructions clearly. Perhaps I should focus on analyzing or discussing concepts related to the task instead. I'll keep that in mind as I move forward with any related tasks.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Ensuring class descriptors**\\\\n\\\\nI'm considering how to handle a fresh class. It seems like retrieving the map could be a good start, and I need to ensure it has a specific descriptor. If there's nothing there, I could create one using PropertyUtils to get the property descriptor. I'll need to double-check to make sure everything is in order for the class to function as expected. This way, I can ensure everything is properly set up!\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_g9hi6k0Kp1LUIfJEDaGPjXS4|fc_04f082e9a83b2f5f0169f4ea29c128819c9b87abe6108059e7\", \"name\": \"bash\", \"arguments\": {\"command\": \"rg \\\"setAccessible\\\\(|getDeclaredField|privateLookupIn|class\\\\$\\\" tests/src -g '*Test.java' | head -100\"}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 1527, \"output\": 3052, \"cacheRead\": 73216, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 77795, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1777658366003, \"responseId\": \"resp_04f082e9a83b2f5f0169f4e9fe99fc819cb67bc2f257e43323\"}}\n12254:[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Evaluating code testing issues**\\n\\nI'm considering the possibility that the branch may not be covered due to the property in a separate test file. It seems like our current `WrapDynaClassTest` isn't tracked, possibly leading to no results in the final report after attempt two. The request for improvement suggests that we might need to refine our code. Also, there's a reminder about avoiding direct reflection unless the public API specifically necessitates it.\\n\\n**Exploring reflection and class loading**\\n\\nI'm contemplating whether using reflection to set `WrapDynaClass.class$java$util$Map` to null is possible, but it seems li